TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {11258=Spring 2014: Selected to the All-Ivy League singles second team and doubles first team … Finished the season ranked No. 21 in doubles with partner Kanika Vaidya … Went 12-3 in dual matches, playing primarily as the No. 2 … Defeated Amanda Muliawan from Princeton, 6-0, 6-1 at the ECAC Championships … Beat Albany’s Cheryl Kukkonen in the top spot, 6-0, 6-1 … Downed Harvard’s June Lee in straight sets … Outlasted Dartmouth’s Taylor Ng for a three-set win … Turned away Penn’s Kana Daniel, 6-2, 6-1 … Victorious against Kentucky’s Aldilia Sutjiadi in the NCAA Tournament, 7-6, 6-1 … Compiled a 15-3 doubles mark with partner Kanika Vaidya as the Lions top pair …Went 6-1 against the Ivy League … Shutout Denver’s Schnell/Van Genechten … Blanked Boyer/Garcia from UC Santa Barbara … Won top doubles match over Kentucky’s McGraw/Witten at the NCAA Tournament.}
textBeforeTable: Personal: English major ... Daughter of Margaret and Jean-Claude Sanon … Member of the National Honor Society, the National Spanish Honor Society and the National Society of High School Scholars … National Achievement Participant … Principal's Honor Roll.   Miami Herald Scholar Athlete and Broward County Athletic Association's Scholar Athlete (2010). Sun Sentinel Girls' Tennis Player of the Year in 2010 … Member of FHSAA STate Championship team ('07,'08) … two-time individual FHSAA singles state champion ('09,'10) … Two-time FHSAA doubles state champion ('07, '08) … Went undefeated in her senior season, playing a perfect 12-0 in #1 singles … finished her high school career with a 52-2 overall record … Named At St. Thomas Aquinas: Three time letter-winner in tennis … Team captain her senior year … two-time All Broward Girls' Tennis Player of the Year ('09,'10) … Named Fall 2010: Seeded No.3 at the Columbia Invitational in the A Singles Draw … Advanced to the semifinals with wins over players from St. John’s and Penn, before falling to the No.1 seed … Participating in the B singles draw at the USTA National Tennis Center Invitational, winning over a player from Seton Hall in the first round … Advanced to the semifinals of the doubles main draw at the ITA Northeast Regionals with partner Nicole Bartnik … Had wins over pairs from NJIT, Quinnipiac, the No.3 seed from Harvard and the No.6 seed from Binghamton, before
